Case No. 1,114. BAUGH v. NOLAND. [2 Cranch, C. C. 2.] 1 Circuit Court, District of Columbia. June Term, 1810. Bail—Insolvent. The defendant had been discharged under the insolvent law of Maryland, in 1809, since the cause of action. The bail produced a copy of the record of discharge, and an ex-oneretur was allowed.
